hospitals,
state and federal institutions, and private research organizations who are authorities in the given field of investigation in their ._
foundation auspices to the specialists located in the public or quasi-public
institutions. This approach conceals from the institution the interest of
CIA and permits the recipient to proceed with his investigation, publish
hisfindings (excluding intelligence implications), and account for his
expenditures in a manner normal to his institution. A number of the
grants have included funds for the construction and equipping of restearclij
own right. Emnual grants of funds are made under ostensible research '

